               <occupation type="literary"> traditional painter </occupation>
               <birth when="1872"></birth>
               
               
               <floruit notBefore="1882" notAfter="1942"> He was a traditional Ethiopian painter. He received a traditional church education
                  in <placeName ref="INS0354DB">Dabra Bizan</placeName>.  
                  After his ordination as a deacon, <persName ref="PRS3887estazya">ʾƎsṭazyā</persName> continued his education in qǝne bet and Zemā bet. 
                  He studied church painting in the same monastery, possibly under the guidance of <persName ref="PRS4228GabraGi">Gabra Giyorgis</persName> from 
                  <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</placeName>.
                  It seems that <persName ref="PRS3887estazya">ʾƎsṭazyā</persName>'s main interest was monumental wall-painting. 
                  He painted murals in the churches of <placeName ref="LOC5932Tegray">Tǝgrāy</placeName>, 
                  <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>and <placeName ref="LOC2991Eritre">Eritrea</placeName>. </floruit>
               <death when="1942"></death>
               
               
